### Capstone Project : Colorectal Database
Colonoscopy and endoscope video have proven to have a high risk of misinterpretation by medical staff due
the length of the digestive system, the amount of unideal structures depicted, and patients lack of adherence to
fasting prior to the procedure. It can be very difficult to identify, diagnose, and track things found in the
digestive tract such as polyps which have the potential to develop into a tumor. By developing a repository that
documents threatening structures such as: polyps, diverticulitis, hemorrhoids, inflamed tissue from IBS, and
the like we may find trends in patient health, as well as better survey imminent danger. This project aims to
circumvent the issue of human error in misdiagnosing patients by stating the likelihood of diseased sites
developing in further stages, as well as more clearly document issues in a given patient's digestive system.

For this database I built compiles real world data on colorectal cancer (CRC) and polyps based upon physician 
observations. In this database we gain the ability to document observations, categorize them, and find accuracy 
scores for individual physician predictions. 
